More than 200 firefighters, backed up by 40 fire engines, have spent more than 12 hours trying to extinguish the Grenfell Tower blaze. JOHANNESBURG - Police have announced the death toll at the Grenfell Tower blaze in London now stands at 12.More than 200 firefighters, backed up by 40 fire engines, have spent more than 12 hours trying to extinguish the Grenfell Tower blaze.So far 65 people have been rescued, while hospitals are treating around 70 others, including firefighters.